Multichar_Symbols  !!вүҲ # Definitions for @CODE@

!! ## Tags for POS

 +N      !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = Noun
 +A      !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = Adjective
 +Adv    !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = Adverb
 +V      !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = Verb
 +Pron   !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = Pronouns
 +CS     !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = Subjunction
 +CC     !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = Conjunction
 +Po     !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = Postposition
 +Pr     !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = Preposition
 +Interj !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = Interjection
 +Pcle   !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = Particle
 +Num    !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = Numeral
 +TODO   !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = Code for items that have not been modeled yet
 +Dyn    !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = Code dynamic acronyms

!! ### Tags for sub-POS

 +Prop    !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = Propernouns
 +ACR     !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = Acronym
 +TEL     !!= `@CODE` = telephone number (beta testings)

!! ### Pronoun subtypes

 +Pers    !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = Personal pronoun
 +Dem     !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = Demonstrative pronoun
 +Interr  !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = Interrogative pronoun
 +Refl    !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = reflexive pronoun
 +Recipr  !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = reciprocal pronoun
 +Rel     !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = relative pronoun
 +Indef   !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = indefinite pronoun
 +Coll    !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = collective numerals
 +Arab    !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = arabic numerals
 +Rom     !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = remertall

!! ## Error tags

!! All Err-tags must have a normative form as lemma except Err/Lex

 +Err/Orth         !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = Substandard. An ungrammatical, non-normative form of normative lemma.
 +Err/Lex          !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = No normative lemma
 +Err/Cmp          !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = No normative compound, often wrong first part of cmp (in other case than nom or gen, or adv og pronoun)
 +Err/Der          !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = Lemmas that break with regular derivation rules, both morphologically and semantically
 +Err/Infl         !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = Lemmas that break with normative inflection rules, often used with morphological changes
 +Err/MissingSpace !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = indicates that there is a missing space, causing an orthographic error. Used for "goadedagi", when it should be "goade dagi"
 +Err/Hyph         !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = when there is a hyphen where none should have been
 +Err/SpaceCmp     !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = used for compounds written apart - only retained in the HFST Grammar Checker disambiguation analyser


!! ## Usage restriction tags

 +Use/Marg         !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** вҖ“ Marginal, but normative lemmas. Not in speller.
 +Use/-Spell       !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** вҖ“ Excluded from speller
 +Use/-PLX         !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** вҖ“ Excluded from PLX speller
 +Use/-PMatch      !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** вҖ“ Do not include in fst's made for hfst-pmatch
 +Use/SpellNoSugg  !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** вҖ“ Recognized, but not suggested in speller
 +Use/Circ         !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** вҖ“ Circular path
 +Use/CircN        !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** вҖ“ Circular number path
 +Use/Ped          !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** вҖ“ Remove from pedagogical speller
 +Use/NG           !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** вҖ“ Do not generate, only for Oahpa and MT. In speller.
 +Use/MT           !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** вҖ“ Generate for MT only, for restricting analyses needed
 +Use/NGminip      !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** вҖ“ Not for miniparadigm in VD dicts
 +Use/NotDNorm     !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** вҖ“ For words without formal normalization. Divvun suggest that this shouldn't be normative.
 +Use/DNorm        !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** вҖ“ For words without formal normalization.  Divvun suggest that this should be normative. Included in speller.
 +Use/PMatch       !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** вҖ“ Only use in fst's targeted for `hfst-pmatch`
 +Use/Derrog       !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** вҖ“ Derrogatory word. Recognized, but not suggested in speller, same as SpellNoSugg
 +Use/GC           !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** вҖ“ **only** retained in the HFST Grammar Checker disambiguation analyser
 +Use/-GC          !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** вҖ“ **never** retained in the HFST Grammar Checker disambiguation analyser
 +Use/TTS          !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** вҖ“ **only** retained in the HFST Text-To-Speech disambiguation tokeniser
 +Use/-TTS         !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** вҖ“ **never** retained in the HFST Text-To-Speech disambiguation tokeniser

!! ## Dialect and Area tags
 +Area/SE     !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** - Used in Sweden only
 +Area/NO     !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** - Used in Norway only
 +Dial/N      !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** Used in the northern areas.  Some might say that
              !!    these words are sme-words, but they are used by lulesamis in
              !!    the northern part of the dialect area. Words like "vГЎlmas"
 +Dial/S      !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** Used in the southern areas
 +Dial/SH     !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** Short forms

!! ## Compounding tags

!! The tags are of the following form:
!! * **+CmpNP/xxx** - Normative (N), Position (P), ie. the tag describes what
!!                    position the tagged word can be in in a compound
!! * **+CmpN/xxx**  - Normative (N) **form** ie. the tag describes what
!!                    form the tagged word should use when making compounds
!! * **+Cmp/xxx**   - Descriptive compounding tags, ie. tags that*describes*
!!                    what form a word actually is using in a compound

!! ### Normative/prescriptive compounding tags

!! These govern compound behaviour for normative tools like the speller, ie. what a compound **SHOULD BE**.

!! The first part of the component may be ..
+CmpN/Sg          !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = Singular
+CmpN/SgN         !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = Singular Nominative
+CmpN/SgG         !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = Singular Genitive
+CmpN/PlG         !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = Plural Genitive
+CmpN/Attr        !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** = Attributive

!! This part of the component can ..

+CmpNP/All       !!вүҲ * @CODE@ - ... be in all positions, **default**, this tag does not have to be written
+CmpNP/First     !!вүҲ * @CODE@ - ... only be first part in a compound or alone
+CmpNP/Pref      !!вүҲ * @CODE@ - ... only **first** part in a compound, NEVER alone
+CmpNP/Last      !!вүҲ * @CODE@ - ... only be last part in a compound or alone
+CmpNP/Suff      !!вүҲ * @CODE@ - ... only **last** part in a compound, NEVER alone
+CmpNP/None      !!вүҲ * @CODE@ - ... not take part in compounds
+CmpNP/Only      !!вүҲ * @CODE@ - ... only be part of a compound, i.e. can never
                 !!                 be used alone, but can appear in any position

!! The second part of the compound may require that the previous (left part) is (and thus overrides the regular CmpN tags):

+CmpN/SgLeft     !!вүҲ * @CODE@  Singular to the left
+CmpN/SgNomLeft  !!вүҲ * @CODE@  Singular nominative to the left
+CmpN/SgGenLeft  !!вүҲ * @CODE@  Singular genitive to the left
+CmpN/PlGenLeft  !!вүҲ * @CODE@  Plural genitive to the left

!! But these tags can again be overriden by the first word in a compound, if this part of the compound is tagged with a def tag:

+CmpN/Def        !!вүҲ * **@CODE@**  Left override
+CmpN/DefSgGen   !!вүҲ * **@CODE@**  Overrides left tag, requires SgGen form
+CmpN/DefPlGen   !!вүҲ * **@CODE@**  Overrides left tag, requires PlGen form

!! ## Descriptive compounding tags
!! Tags for compound analysis - this is what a compound actually is.
!! Some of these tags are also used in combination with the
!! above normative tags to actually enforce compound restrictions in the fst.

 +Cmp/Sg       !!вүҲ * **@CODE@**  Singular
 +Cmp/SgNom    !!вүҲ * **@CODE@**  Singular Nominative
 +Cmp/SgGen    !!вүҲ * **@CODE@**  Singular Genitive
 +Cmp/PlGen    !!вүҲ * **@CODE@**  Plural Genitiv
 +Cmp/PlNom    !!вүҲ * **@CODE@**  Plural Nominative
 +Cmp/Attr     !!вүҲ * **@CODE@**  Attribute
 +Cmp/Sh       !!вүҲ * **@CODE@**  testing ShCmp
 +Cmp/Long     !!вүҲ * **@CODE@**  Long for om SgNom when short form is default, tjГҘhkaNIBMEbievddegirjje and bierjjeDAHKAiehket
 +Cmp/Unass    !!вүҲ * **@CODE@**  Unassimiled as first part of Cmp, e.g. telegram- in stead for telegrГЎmma-
 +Cmp          !!вүҲ * **@CODE@**  Dynamic compound - this tag should always be part of a dynamic compound.
               !!                It is important for Apertium, and useful in other cases as well.
 +Cmp/SplitR   !!вүҲ * **@CODE@**  This is a split compound with the other part to the right:
               !!                "Arbeids- og inkluderingsdepartementet" => Arbeids- = +Cmp/SplitR
 +Cmp/SplitL   !!вүҲ * **@CODE@**  This is a split compound with the other part to the left
 +Cmp/Hyph    !!вүҲ Compound with (optional) hyphen, heavily weighted
 +Cmp/OblHyph !!вүҲ Obligatory hyphen, not as badly weighed as +Cmp/Hyph


!! # Inflectional Tags
