!! ## Flag diacritics

!! We have manually optimised the structure of our lexicon using following
!! flag diacritics to restrict morhpological combinatorics - only allow compounds
!! with verbs if the verb is further derived into a noun again:

!! |               Flag diacritic | Explanation
!! |               :------------- |:-----------
 @P.NeedNoun.ON@    !!вүҲ |  @CODE@ | (Dis)allow compounds with verbs unless nominalised
 @D.NeedNoun.ON@    !!вүҲ |  @CODE@ | (Dis)allow compounds with verbs unless nominalised
 @C.NeedNoun@       !!вүҲ |  @CODE@ | (Dis)allow compounds with verbs unless nominalised


!! |               Flag diacritic | Explanation
!! |               :------------- |:-----------
 @P.Pmatch.Loc@       !!вүҲ |  @CODE@ | Used on multi-token analyses; tell hfst-tokenise/pmatch where in the form/analysis the token should be split. Used e.g. in `bijladagi` to split `bijla` from `dagi`, or after abbreviations with full stops before the full stop, to allow an alternate `+CLB` analysis of it in case of a sentence final abbreviation. __NB!__ This will give a faulty lemma for the abbreviation, as it will not include the full stop. This can lead to other issues, but presently we have no other solution if we want to keep the full stopp as a separate token. We could leave a full stop at the end of the abbreviation lemma as well (but not on the input side - we only have one full stop in the input). That must be tested, it could work, but then requires special attention when generating suggestions in e.g. grammar checkers - it should not generate two full stops. 
 @P.Pmatch.Backtrack@ !!вүҲ |  @CODE@ | Used on single-token analyses; tell hfst-tokenise/pmatch to backtrack by reanalysing the substrings before and after this point in the form (to find combinations of shorter analyses that would otherwise be missed)


!! |               Flag diacritic | Explanation
!! |               :------------- |:-----------
 @D.ErrOrth.ON@      !!вүҲ | @CODE@ | To be written
 @R.ErrOrth.ON@      !!вүҲ | @CODE@ | To be written
 @C.ErrOrth@         !!вүҲ | @CODE@ | To be written
 @P.ErrOrth.ON@      !!вүҲ | @CODE@ | To be written


!! For languages that allow compounding, the following flag diacritics are needed
!! to control position-based compounding restrictions for nominals. Their use is
!! handled automatically if combined with +CmpN/xxx tags. If not used, they will
!! do no harm.

!! |              Flag diacritic | Explanation
!! |              :------------- |:-----------
 @P.CmpFrst.FALSE@ !!вүҲ |  @CODE@ | Require that words tagged as such only appear first
 @D.CmpPref.TRUE@  !!вүҲ |  @CODE@ | Block such words from entering ENDLEX
 @P.CmpPref.FALSE@ !!вүҲ |  @CODE@ | Block these words from making further compounds
 @D.CmpLast.TRUE@  !!вүҲ |  @CODE@ | Block such words from entering R
 @D.CmpNone.TRUE@  !!вүҲ |  @CODE@ | Combines with the next tag to prohibit compounding
 @U.CmpNone.FALSE@ !!вүҲ |  @CODE@ | Combines with the prev tag to prohibit compounding
 @U.CmpNone.TRUE@  !!вүҲ |  @CODE@ | Combines with the two previous ones to block compounding
 @P.CmpOnly.TRUE@  !!вүҲ |  @CODE@ | Sets a flag to indicate that the word has passed R
 @D.CmpOnly.FALSE@ !!вүҲ |  @CODE@ | Disallow words coming directly from root.
 @U.CmpHyph.FALSE@ !!вүҲ |  @CODE@ | Flag to control hyphenated compounds like proper nouns
 @U.CmpHyph.TRUE@  !!вүҲ |  @CODE@ | Flag to control hyphenated compounds like proper nouns
 @C.CmpHyph@       !!вүҲ |  @CODE@ | Flag to control hyphenated compounds like proper nouns
 

!! Use the following flag diacritics to control downcasing of derived proper
!! nouns (e.g. Finnish Pariisi -> pariisilainen). See e.g. North SГЎmi for how to use
!! these flags. There exists a ready-made regex that will do the actual down-casing
!! given the proper use of these flags.

!! |           Flag diacritic | Explanation
!! |           :------------- |:-----------
 @U.Cap.Obl@    !!вүҲ |  @CODE@ | Disallow downcasing of names when not derived: Deatnu
 @U.Cap.Opt@    !!вүҲ |  @CODE@ | Allowing downcasing of derived names: deatnulasj.
 @P.Px.add@     !!вүҲ |  @CODE@ | Giving possibility for Px-suffixes (all except from Nom 3.p)
 @R.Px.add@     !!вүҲ |  @CODE@ | Requiring P.Px.add-flag for Px-suffixes (all except from Nom 3.p)
 @P.Nom3Px.add@ !!вүҲ |  @CODE@ | Giving possibility for Px-suffixes Nom 3.p
 @R.Nom3Px.add@ !!вүҲ |  @CODE@ | Requiring P.Nom3Px.add flag for Px-suffixes Nom 3.p

@R.SpellRlx.ON@ !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** Flag used to tag spell-relax-analysed strings (and only those).
@D.SpellRlx.ON@ !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** Flag used to tag spell-relax-analysed strings (and only those).
@C.SpellRlx@    !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** Flag used to tag spell-relax-analysed strings (and only those).

@R.SpaceCmp.ON@ !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** Flag to tag compounds written with a space
@D.SpaceCmp.ON@ !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** Flag to tag compounds written with a space
@C.SpaceCmp@    !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** Flag to tag compounds written with a space+


!! |              Flag diacritic | Explanation
